		Types of classes-- General concepts not actual types
1. Normal Class  -- Concreate class
2. Abstract class -- Object can not created
3. Parent Class -- Providing properties
4. Child Class -- Acquiring properties
5. Java Bean --  Private properties --- Getter and Setters  -Reusable component
6. Adapter class - Empty implementation of Interface methods
7. Public Class -- class name and Source file name must be same.   Can be access in all packages.
8. Default class-- access within the package
9. Tightly encapsulated class -- Class contains private properties
10. Implementation class  -- Implementing Interface methods
11. Final class -- Can not extend this class
12. Immutable classes -- Once object is created of this class we can not modify the existing objects
13. Mutable classes -- Once object is created of this class we can modify the existing objects
14 Strict FP classes -- Floating point calculation will follow IEEE 754 standards
15 Singleton class -- Allows only one object to be created.

		Modifiers
	Default    
	-- in java default modifier is default 
	-- Applicable for variables, classes, constructors, methods
	-- Access within the package
	Public
	--
	Protected
	Private